cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SI

The paper discusses the use of computer vision approaches to analyze images in the context of human rights violations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the challenges of identifying and verifying images, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the potential of social media networks to share images, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
